The paper deals with population protocols, which are a type of distributed computing model, and presents protocols for two specific problems: leader election and exact majority voting. These problems are related to distributed computing and algorithms, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as it specifically deals with distributed computing models. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper deals with interactions between agents in a network. cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper relies on probabilistic facts. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also possible categories as the paper presents algorithms for specific problems.
